    <title>iFixit now sells a USB-powered tool for removing the iPhone 16’s battery</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="A USB-C cable attached to a portable power source is connected to the iFixit VoltClip tool, which is connected to the battery in an iPhone 16." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TsGkCecKwCVVpP4s7af6ZMT5XJc=/1x0:1600x1066/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73639581/voltclip3.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;iFixit’s VoltClip offers an alternative to buying another disposable 9V battery.&lt;/em&gt; | Image: iFixit&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="nCV9cD"&gt;Apple recommends removing the iPhone 16’s battery, which is held in place with a new &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/28/24188099/apple-might-try-electrically-induced-adhesive-debonding-on-iphone-batteries"&gt;electrically debondable adhesive&lt;/a&gt;, by using a 9V battery and some alligator clips. &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifixit.com%2Fproducts%2Fvoltclip&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F10%2F8%2F24262373%2Fifixit-iphone-16-battery-repair-adhesive" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;iFixit’s new USB-powered VoltClip&lt;/a&gt; is an alternative tool that eliminates the need for a disposable battery, while also potentially speeding up the debonding process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="ijd0bW"&gt;The VoltClip, available now for $10.95 through iFixit’s online store, features a pair of alligator clips attached to short wires on one end and a 12V DC adapter on the other that converts a barrel connector to a USB-C port.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class="e-image"&gt;
        
      &lt;cite&gt;Image: iFixit&lt;/cite&gt;
      &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;iFixit’s USB-C powered VoltClip is now available for $10.95 but doesn’t include a USB power source.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p id="z5rVqH"&gt;When &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifixit.com%2FGuide%2FHow%2Bto%2BUse%2Bthe%2BVoltClip%2Bto%2BDebond%2Ban%2BiPhone%2BBattery%2BAdhesive%2F177712&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F10%2F8%2F24262373%2Fifixit-iphone-16-battery-repair-adhesive" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;plugged into a device&lt;/a&gt; that supports USB-C...&lt;/p&gt;
